 <fr:p>By induction on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>; the base cases for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n=-2]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n=-1]]></fr:tex> are given by <fr:ref
addr="erct-002V"
taxon="Corollary" /> and <fr:ref
addr="erct-0026"
taxon="Lemma" /> respectively. In the inductive step, we assume that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> exhibits <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> as a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0025.xml"
addr="erct-0025"
title="Retract">retract</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and that for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> the identification type <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x=_Ay]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001G.xml"
addr="erct-001G"
title="N-truncated type"><html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n+1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:link> to show that for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u,v:B]]></fr:tex> the identification type <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u=_Bv]]></fr:tex> is likewise <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001G.xml"
addr="erct-001G"
title="N-truncated type"><html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n+1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:link>. The result follows from our assumption and the fact that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u=_Bv]]></fr:tex> is (by <fr:ref
addr="erct-003U"
taxon="Lemma" />) a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0025.xml"
addr="erct-0025"
title="Retract">retract</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[su=_Asv]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
